			<div class="author">by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=34659&amp;sid=469102a612be38316c03a171bfcf5c2f">notarat</a></strong> &raquo; Mon Nov 05, 2012 3:36 pm </div>

			

			<div class="content"><blockquote><div><cite>Aydan wrote:</cite>You wont be able to power a SSD or HDD from an unmodified Raspberry.<br />The USB ports have 140mA fuses in them.</div></blockquote><br /><br />I know I'm necro'ing this post, but this is false information.<br /><br />I can connect a 480GB Corsair Force GT SSD directly to the Pi and power it just fine.<br /><br />I also tried this with a 60GB Corsair Force 3 SSD with zero problems.<br /><br />This is on a 256MB Pi and a 512MB Pi.<br /><br />Just trying to get updated information out there in case someone is intersted in this type of setup.</div>

			

